JOHANNESBURG - One Political Analyst believes Deputy President Cyril Ramaphosa has thrown his hat in the ring, to become ANC President. On Sunday Ramaphosa said that the party will continue to lose power, if claims of state capture are left unchecked.He said he believes the ANC should support the call for a commission of inquiry into allegations of state capture.Ramaphosa was speaking at a Chris Hani memorial lecture in Uitenhage in the Eastern Cape. The ANC therefore must, should support the establishment of an effective, credible mechanism to investigate these claims. I support that there be a judicial commission of inquiry...It is the truth that will unite our movement once again. We can not leave this matter unattended. Sazi ukuthi it is causing problems within our ranks, said the deputy president.WATCH: Ramaphosa calls for state capture inquiry eNCA